Off to Germany?!!! I was going to go there when I went to Europe in 2008 but we decided to just be non- tourists. Spent a lot of time in the UK. Liverpool for a week!! My friends conference but we had a gorgeous paid for apartment and I got a photo with John Lennon! I also had time to get over the 23/24 hr flight with a chronic back! Then Manchester for a few days (my friend left there aged 10 to come to Australia). London for a week (thank God for the East end flat we rented!). Then Paris for 2 weeks to play the flaneur. 7 flights of stairs to our tiny apartment right next to the Bastille town hall 10 days before Bastille day! Music every day and night. Happy people, Pickpockets, great patisseries(?). A short walk into the Marais district. Fabulous. I love Paris. We decided to only go to Paris and really breathe the life in rather than flit around to a few other countries. I hope you had/ are having a good time. Berlin was the next city on our list. A mink story. XX mink
